Unix timestamp of now<br>
{{moment}}<br><br>

Current time with formatting <br>
{{moment format="HH:mm:ss"}}<br><br>

Specific time with formatting<br>
{{moment sampledate format="HH:mm:ss"}}<br><br>

Specific unix timestamp with formatting<br>
{{moment unixtimestamp format="HH:mm:ss"}}<br><br>

Specific datetime with formatting<br>
{{moment sampledate format="dddd, DD MMMM YYYY HH:mm:ss ZZ"}}<br><br>

Language support<br>
{{moment sampledate lang="fi" format="dddd, DD MMMM YYYY HH:mm:ss ZZ"}}<br><br>

Is the added date valid?<br>
{{moment sampledate isValid=null}}<br><br>

Input as a string, with defined format<br>
{{moment [sampletextdate,"ddd, DD MMM YYYY HH:mm:ss ZZ"] format="MMMM YYYY"}}<br><br>

Multiple formats, moment.js tries to figure out what's the correct one<br>
{{moment [sampletextdate,formats] format="MMMM YYYY"}}<br><br>

Specific datetime with formatting, converted to utc<br>
{{moment sampledate utc=null format="dddd, DD MMMM YYYY HH:mm:ss ZZ"}}<br><br>

Getters and setters, example: get week of year, depends on lang (see (moment.js)[http://momentjs.com/docs/#/get-set/] documentation for more details)<br>
The week number in Finland is {{moment sampledate lang="fi" week=null}}<br><br>

Manipulate, example: add days, (see (moment.js)[http://momentjs.com/docs/#/manipulating/] documentation for more details)<br>
{{moment sampledate format="dddd"}}-{{moment sampledate add=daysadd format="dddd"}}<br><br>

Manipulate, example: subtract years, (see (moment.js)[http://momentjs.com/docs/#/manipulating/] documentation for more details)<br>
{{moment sampledate subtract=fiveyearsago format="YYYY"}}-{{moment sampledate format="YYYY"}}<br><br>

Manipulate, example: startOf month, (see (moment.js)[http://momentjs.com/docs/#/manipulating/] documentation for more details)<br>
{{moment sampledate startOf="month" format="dddd, DD MMMM YYYY HH:mm:ss ZZ"}}<br><br>

Manipulate, example: endOf week, (see (moment.js)[http://momentjs.com/docs/#/manipulating/] documentation for more details)<br>
{{moment sampledate endOf="week" format="dddd, DD MMMM YYYY HH:mm:ss ZZ"}}<br><br>

Time from now<br>
After this page is rendered, the week will end {{moment endOf="week" fromNow=null}}<br><br>

Time from X<br>
This helper was coded {{moment from=sampledate}}<br><br>

Calendar time<br>
The coding started {{moment sampledate calendar=null}}<br><br>

Diff<br>
The difference between those two moments is {{moment diff=sampledate}}<br><br>

Days in Month<br>
This month has {{moment daysInMonth=null}} days<br><br>

Days in Month<br>
This month has {{moment daysInMonth=null}} days<br><br>

Duration, with humanization<br>
The event will last {{duration duration humanize=null}}<br><br>

The moment.js has plenty of features and these examples are just the tip of the iceberg of what moment.js can do.
Just remember, in \{{moment method=null}} means moment().method() and \{{moment somedate method="something"}} means moment(somedate).method("something"). Also, the handlebars syntax does not let you pass some values (like arrays and objects) directly from the tag, so you may need to use the yaml frontmatter to run those.
